 assume that Git is available. Normally, generated tests run on Ubuntu, and I won’t be using Docker. I should probably read the documentation for usage details. I’m curious if I’ll find that the gitexe provider depends on the Git command-line executable. \\n\\nI want to fetch documentation for dependencies and the source quickly, as that will help clarify things. I’m not sure what to confirm in the final summary just yet!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_WX7Y2hNr8yuk4YVQLtgoyhVA|fc_0c5d937aef40678a016a28a85a9abc81909a5daa3e83fa0672", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re\nurls=[\n'https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/dependencies.html',\n'https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/xref/org/apache/maven/scm/provider/git/gitexe/GitExeScmProvider.html',\n'https://maven.apache.org/scm/maven-scm-providers/maven-scm-providers-git/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/apidocs/org/apache/maven/scm/provider/git/gitexe/GitExeScmProvider.html'\n]\nfor url in urls:\n print('\\nURL', url)\n try:\n  html=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n  text=re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',html)\n  text=re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',text)\n  for key in ['git','dependency','Git Executable','command']:\n   idx=text.lower().find(key.lower())\n   if idx>=0:\n    print(text[max(0,idx-300):idx+900])\n    break\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 40}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2V5V224rVxNjSQG2LVRwAQ6R|fc_0c5d937aef40678a016a28a85a9ad081908b9d17f5ba6c9af1", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, zipfile, io\nurl='https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/apache/maven/scm/maven-scm-provider-gitexe/1.11.1/maven-scm-provider-gitexe-1.11.1.jar'\ntry:\n data=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=30).read()\n print('jar bytes', len(data))\n z=zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(d